{
  "texts": [
    "Abstract-Emerging multimodal large language models (MLLMs) exhibit great potential for chart question answering (CQA).",
    "Recent efforts primarily focus on scaling up training datasets (i.e., charts, data tables, and question-answer (QA) pairs) through data collection and synthesis.",
    "However, our empirical study on existing MLLMs and CQA datasets reveals notable gaps.",
    "First, current data collection and synthesis focus on data volume and lack consideration of fine-grained visual encodings and QA tasks, resulting in unbalanced data distribution divergent from practical CQA scenarios.",
    "Second, existing work follows the training recipe of the base MLLMs initially designed for natural images, under-exploring the adaptation to unique chart characteristics, such as rich text elements."
  ]
}